#: ../../D/diff.rst:5
msgid "diff"
msgstr "diff"

#: ../../D/diff.rst:7
msgid "/dif/, n\\."
msgstr "/dif/, 名詞"

#: ../../D/diff.rst:10
msgid ""
"A change listing, especially giving differences between (and additions to) "
"source code or documents (the term is often used in the plural diffs). "
"\"Send me your diffs for the Jargon File!\" Compare :ref:`vdiff`\\."
msgstr ""
"変更のリスト。特にソースコードや文書の間の差異(と追加)を示すもの(この用語はしばしば複数形のdiffsで使われる)。「Send me your "
"diffs for the Jargon File!」(Jargon Fileの君のdiffを送ってくれ!)。\\ :ref:`vdiff`\\ "
"と比較せよ。"

#: ../../D/diff.rst:15
msgid ""
"Specifically, such a listing produced by the :manpage:`diff(1)` command, "
"esp. when used as specification input to the :manpage:`patch(1)` utility "
"(which can actually perform the modifications; see :ref:`patch`\\). This is "
"a common method of distributing patches and source updates in the Unix/C "
"world."
msgstr ""
"具体的には、\\ :manpage:`diff(1)`\\ コマンドによって生成される、特に\\ :manpage:`patch(1)`\\ "
"ユーティリティ(実際に変更を実行できる。\\ :ref:`patch`\\ "
"を参照)への仕様入力として使われるときの、そのようなリスト。これはUnix/Cの世界でパッチやソース更新を配布するよくある方法である。"

#: ../../D/diff.rst:19
msgid ""
"v\\. To compare (whether or not by use of automated tools on machine-"
"readable files); see also :ref:`vdiff`\\, :ref:`mod`\\."
msgstr ""
"動詞。比較すること(機械可読ファイルに対して自動ツールを使うか否かを問わず)。\\ :ref:`vdiff`\\ 、\\ :ref:`mod`\\ "
"も参照。"
